---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About - Haystack Labs"
  description="Learn about Haystack Labs, an experimental craft & technology research residency program bringing together artists, designers, scientists, and makers to explore the integration of emerging technologies with traditional craft practices."
>
  <article class="about">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="about__hero">
      <div class="about__container">
        <h1 class="about__hero-title">About Haystack Labs</h1>
        <p class="about__hero-description">
          An experimental craft & technology research residency program at
          Haystack Mountain School of Crafts, in partnership with MIT Center for
          Bits and Atoms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What is Haystack Labs -->
    <section class="about__section">
      <div class="about__container">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">What is Haystack Labs?</h2>
        <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-lightbulb -->
        <div class="about__content-grid">
          <div class="about__main-content">
            <p class="about__text">
              Haystack Labs is a one-week experimental program that invites a
              diverse collection of creative professionals from around the world
              to explore the relationship between craft and technology. Over the
              span of the week, participants work on producing new processes,
              tools, machines, and other resources that inform the craft
              community.
            </p>
            <p class="about__text">
              This is not a formal conference or summit, but rather a charrette
              where people intensely collaborate during their time at Haystack
              with the intention of producing projects that fall within the
              craft and technology domain.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="about__sidebar">
            <div class="about__stats-card">
              <h3 class="about__stats-title">By the Numbers</h3>
              <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-chart-line -->
              <div class="about__stat-item">
                <span class="about__stat-number">150+</span>
                <span class="about__stat-label">Participants</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about__stat-item">
                <span class="about__stat-number">5</span>
                <span class="about__stat-label">Years Running</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about__stat-item">
                <span class="about__stat-number">40+</span>
                <span class="about__stat-label">Projects</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Brief History -->
    <section class="about__section about__section--dark">
      <div class="about__container">
        <h2 class="about__section-title about__section-title--light">
          A Brief History
        </h2>
        <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-clock-clockwise -->
        <div class="about__timeline">
          <div class="about__timeline-item">
            <div class="about__timeline-year">2021</div>
            <div class="about__timeline-content">
              <h3 class="about__timeline-title">The Pilot Program</h3>
              <p class="about__timeline-text">
                Haystack Mountain School of Crafts and the MIT Center for Bits
                and Atoms developed and piloted the first experimental
                residential program (July 12-16). The week brought together
                artists and scientists to explore the integration of emerging
                technologies and processes for craft. 12 projects emerged from
                the week, including ClayStack ceramic 3D printing, Urumbot
                drawing machine, and pop-up bio labs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__timeline-item">
            <div class="about__timeline-year">2022</div>
            <div class="about__timeline-content">
              <h3 class="about__timeline-title">Expansion and Growth</h3>
              <p class="about__timeline-text">
                The program expanded to include a broader collection of people
                from both craft and digital fabrication communities (May 23-27).
                Over 40 people participated and contributed to various
                innovative projects. New equipment was donated, including a
                Form3L SLA printer, ShopBot Rotary Indexer, and Bantam CNC
                machine.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__timeline-item">
            <div class="about__timeline-year">2023</div>
            <div class="about__timeline-content">
              <h3 class="about__timeline-title">Community Building</h3>
              <p class="about__timeline-text">
                The program featured 40 speakers across 5 nights of
                presentations, covering topics from computer science and coding
                to design innovation and computational design. Participants
                included professors, artists, researchers, and industry leaders
                from institutions like MIT, Stanford, Tufts University, and
                companies like New Balance and Topologic.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__timeline-item">
            <div class="about__timeline-year">2024</div>
            <div class="about__timeline-content">
              <h3 class="about__timeline-title">
                Sustainability and Innovation
              </h3>
              <p class="about__timeline-text">
                Held September 6-9, the program focused on projects including
                lattice structures, bioplastics, metal clay experiments,
                biomaterials, large format 3D printing, and electronic sensors.
                The program continued to emphasize open-source documentation and
                collaborative innovation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__timeline-item">
            <div class="about__timeline-year">2025</div>
            <div class="about__timeline-content">
              <h3 class="about__timeline-title">Looking Forward</h3>
              <p class="about__timeline-text">
                Building on five years of success, Haystack Labs continues to
                evolve as a unique incubation space for craft-technology
                innovation, fostering collaborations between artists, makers,
                researchers, and industry partners.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Program Format -->
    <section class="about__section">
      <div class="about__container">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">Program Format</h2>
        <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-calendar-check -->
        <div class="about__format-grid">
          <div class="about__format-card">
            <h3 class="about__format-title">Semi-Structured Schedule</h3>
            <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-clock -->
            <p class="about__format-text">
              The program features morning planning meetings with all
              participants and evening short presentations. The rest of the day
              depends on what participants are working on and may include pop-up
              demos, tutorials, meetings, collaborative projects, and
              independent studio/lab time.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="about__format-card">
            <h3 class="about__format-title">Daily Expectations</h3>
            <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-users -->
            <p class="about__format-text">
              Participants attend morning planning meetings to share progress
              and seek support from the group. A daily schedule of activities is
              loosely assembled during these meetings. All participants help
              document their projects and contribute to the larger knowledge
              base of technology and craft.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="about__format-card">
            <h3 class="about__format-title">Studio Access</h3>
            <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-wrench -->
            <p class="about__format-text">
              Studio experts in particular craft fields are invited as
              participants to facilitate crossover experimentation within
              studios and guide others through new processes. All studios
              (except Glass) are accessible for participants to interact and
              experiment with.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="about__format-card">
            <h3 class="about__format-title">Evening Presentations</h3>
            <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-presentation-chart -->
            <p class="about__format-text">
              Each evening features rapid-fire artist talks where participants
              have 5 minutes to present their work. These presentations are
              grouped into themes like Art & Impact, Machines and Architectures,
              Materials and Processes, and Design and Interfaces.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Program Goals -->
    <section class="about__section about__section--alt">
      <div class="about__container">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">Program Goals</h2>
        <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-target -->
        <div class="about__goals-list">
          <div class="about__goal-item">
            <div class="about__goal-number">01</div>
            <div class="about__goal-content">
              <h3 class="about__goal-title">Make Technology Accessible</h3>
              <p class="about__goal-text">
                Make technology and experimental processes more accessible for
                artists and creative professionals.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__goal-item">
            <div class="about__goal-number">02</div>
            <div class="about__goal-content">
              <h3 class="about__goal-title">Bring New Knowledge</h3>
              <p class="about__goal-text">
                Bring new ideas, knowledge, and resources to Haystack Mountain
                School of Crafts and the broader craft community.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__goal-item">
            <div class="about__goal-number">03</div>
            <div class="about__goal-content">
              <h3 class="about__goal-title">Professional Development</h3>
              <p class="about__goal-text">
                Provide professional development opportunities for participants
                through collaborative learning and skill sharing.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__goal-item">
            <div class="about__goal-number">04</div>
            <div class="about__goal-content">
              <h3 class="about__goal-title">Document Innovation</h3>
              <p class="about__goal-text">
                Document new technologies and craft processes as they are being
                developed, creating open-source resources for the community.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about__goal-item">
            <div class="about__goal-number">05</div>
            <div class="about__goal-content">
              <h3 class="about__goal-title">Cultivate Community</h3>
              <p class="about__goal-text">
                Cultivate an interdisciplinary community of professionals and
                creatives interested in collaborating on experimental projects.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How to Participate -->
    <section class="about__section about__section--cta">
      <div class="about__container">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">How to Participate</h2>
        <!-- Icon placeholder: ph-hand-waving -->
        <div class="about__participation">
          <p class="about__participation-text">
            Haystack Labs is an invitational program. If you're interested in
            participating, please contact us at <a
              href="mailto:fablab@haystack-mtn.org"
              class="about__email-link">fablab@haystack-mtn.org</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    --section-padding: var(--space-5xl);
  }

  /* Container */
  .about__container {
    max-width: var(--container-7xl);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: var(--space-lg);
  }

  /* Hero Section */
  .about__hero {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--color-haystack-navy) 0%,
      var(--color-dark-teal) 100%
    );
    color: var(--color-text-primary-dark);
    padding: var(--section-padding) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about__hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--font-size-5xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
  }

  .about__hero-description {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    color: var(--color-haystack-light-seafoam-green);
  }

  /* Content Sections */
  .about__section {
    padding: var(--section-padding) 0;
    background: var(--color-background);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .about__section--alt {
    background-color: var(--color-background-secondary);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .about__section--dark {
    background: var(--color-haystack-navy);
    color: var(--color-text-primary-dark);
  }

  .about__section--cta {
    background: var(--color-haystack-light-seafoam-green);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .about__section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    color: inherit;
  }

  .about__section-title--light {
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
  }

  /* Content Grid */
  .about__content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about__content-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .about__text {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    color: inherit;
  }

  /* Stats Card */
  .about__stats-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-haystack-light-seafoam-green);
  }

  .about__stats-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--color-haystack-blue);
  }

  .about__stat-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about__stat-number {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-haystack-blue);
  }

  .about__stat-label {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-wide);
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .about__timeline {
    max-width: var(--container-4xl);
    margin-inline: auto;
    position: relative;
  }

  .about__timeline::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 30px;
    top: 40px;
    bottom: 40px;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--color-haystack-seafoam-green);
  }

  .about__timeline-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    position: relative;
  }

  .about__timeline-year {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-haystack-light-seafoam-green);
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--color-haystack-blue);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .about__timeline-title {
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about__timeline-text {
    color: var(--color-haystack-light-seafoam-green);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about__timeline::before {
      display: none;
    }

    .about__timeline-item {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      text-align: center;
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }
  }

  /* Format Grid */
  .about__format-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about__format-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    border-top: 4px solid var(--color-haystack-blue);
    transition: var(--transition-normal);
  }

  .about__format-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  }

  .about__format-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-haystack-blue);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about__format-text {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Goals Section */
  .about__goals-list {
    max-width: var(--container-4xl);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .about__goal-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .about__goal-number {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-haystack-blue);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .about__goal-title {
    color: inherit;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .about__goal-text {
    color: inherit;
    opacity: 0.8;
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about__goal-item {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      text-align: center;
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }
  }

  /* Participation Section */
  .about__participation {
    max-width: var(--container-md);
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about__participation-text {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: inherit;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about__email-link {
    color: var(--color-haystack-blue);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    transition: var(--transition-normal);
  }

  .about__email-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-dark-teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Mobile Styles */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about {
      --section-padding: var(--space-3xl);
    }

    .about__container {
      padding-inline: var(--space-md);
    }

    .about__hero-title {
      font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    }

    .about__hero-description {
      font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    }

    .about__section-title {
      font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    }

    .about__format-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about__format-card {
      padding: var(--space-lg);
    }
  }
</style>
